**Fold rules under test:** dedupe by id across machines (counts accumulate over DISTINCT session refs); Dismiss => Suppressed and STAYS suppressed when later Observed events arrive (permanence — the compaction pre-commitment); Unsuppress restores Pending; Promote => Promoted; a quarantined Observed folds to Quarantined and is never Pending; malformed journal lines are skipped, not fatal; two journals observing the same claim → one candidate listing both machine ids.

**Steps:** (1) failing tests with multi-machine fixture journals written inline via `tempfile`. (2) Implement. (3) Green. (4) Commit `feat(learn): per-machine inbox journals with fold, dedupe, permanent suppression`.

