Order of operations, each under test: (1) drop sessions whose cwd matches `work_dir` (recursion guard layer 3); (2) drop sessions containing `extract::SENTINEL` in any message (layer 4); (3) scope filter — `Adopted` keeps only `repo_is_adopted(cwd)` (gemini sessions with no recoverable cwd are kept only under `All`); (4) drop sessions older than the baseline cutoff; (5) `redact_secrets` (src/redact.rs:52) over EVERY message before size accounting; (6) sort newest-first by ts and truncate to caps — **over-cap content is dropped, not deferred** (amendment #3): the caller still advances watermarks past everything scanned; `dropped_over_cap` is reported so the run log can say what was cut (no silent caps).

**Steps:** (1) failing tests incl. a fixture message carrying a fake AWS key that must arrive `***REDACTED***`; (2) implement; (3) green; (4) commit `feat(learn): slice assembly — scope, caps, redaction, sentinel guard`.

